quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  104,1,"Woe to every fault-finding backbiter;",footnotes:182835:1
  104,2,"who amasses wealth and counts it over and again.",footnotes:182836:1
  104,3,"He thinks that his wealth will immortalise him forever.",footnotes:182837:1
  104,4,"Nay, he shall be thrown into the Crusher.",footnotes:182838:1|182839:2
  104,5,"And what do you know what the Crusher is?"
  104,6,"It is the Fire kindled by Allah,",footnotes:182840:1
  104,7,"the Fire that shall rise to the hearts (of criminals).",footnotes:182841:1
  104,8,"Verily it will close in upon them,",footnotes:182842:1
  104,9,"in outstretched columns.",footnotes:182843:1
